Durban - The 3-year-old boy who was rescued from a swimming pool by his neighbour has died in hospital. According to Shawn Herbst spokesperson for Netcare 911 medics responded to reports of a drowning in Holzner Avenue,Mariannhill on Wednesday at around noon. "Reports from the scene indicated that a 3-year-old male had allegedly fallen into the home pool and drowned. Neighbours heard the splashing and cries for help and went to investigate, when they saw the child was submerged in the pool. The neighbour jumped the fence to rescue the child." Herbst said when paramedics arrived on scene, CPR had already been initiated by the neighbour. "A full advanced life support resuscitation was initiated on takeover and a pulse successfully regained. The young boy was place on a ventilator and rushed to hospital for further treatment." Herbst said the boy was taken to hospital and died in ICU. "He suffered cardiac arrest," said Herbst. Circumstances leading up to the drowning will be investigated by the Mariannhill SAPS who were on scene. POST 